Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_2332
Response Text: 1) Find ways to fund the arts besides HOT. 2) Individual artists or small orgs that don't have a permanent venue shouldn't be required to figure out how to market to tourists on the Nexus grant. As a well-travelled person who has been seeking out art and music around the world for decades, I can tell you that I simply find venues in those cities and see what is happening, during the dates I am there, then decide which ones to visit. Only venues should be required to market to the public. 3) Scoring grant applications based on the neighborhood the applicant lives in, doesn't make sense to me. I live in a neighborhood with a wide range of rental prices and home values. Just because some of them are on the high end, doesn't mean that we all live in those, esp. if we are artists. It also doesn't mean that there are art or music venues in the neighborhood. 4) The applications are grueling.

